  "prompt": "How many rounds of admission will be conducted for an MBA at NIT Trichy?",
  "response": "The number of admission rounds for the MBA program at NIT Trichy can vary each year and is determined by the institute's admissions policy. Generally, the admissions process is conducted through several rounds, which may include shortlisting based on entrance exam scores (such as CAT), group discussions, and personal interviews. It may also include several waitlist rounds depending on the availability of seats and the response of shortlisted candidates.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding the number of admission rounds for a particular academic year, it is recommended to refer to the official NIT Trichy Department of Management Studies website or to contact the admissions office directly.",
